  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Poor Communication&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Two poor areas this hospital needs to clear up. First, we queued up at the Main Outpatients Department reception desk because there was no one staffing it. When a receptionist did appear he had been going round putting up signs advertising a cake sale. Surely, this could have been done at a time when patients were not waiting to book into their clinics. I also though that, &amp;amp;quot;Hello, I'm ...&amp;amp;quot; was something that was supposed to be standard in the NHS. It appears not so at MRI. No member of staff told whose either their name or their job title with one exception. The consultant we saw told us he was the consultant so we could guess his name as being the one on the appointment letter. The consultant asked me who my partner was and this always happens I find in hospital clinics. Perhaps NHS staff should extent a similar courtesy and identify themselves.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
